#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1411
msgid "Hillshade"
msgstr "Ombrage"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1412
msgid ""
"Outputs a raster with a nice shaded relief effect. It’s very useful for "
"visualizing the terrain. You can optionally specify the azimuth and altitude"
" of the light source, a vertical exaggeration factor and a scaling factor to"
" account for differences between vertical and horizontal units."
msgstr ""
"Génère un raster avec un bel effet de relief ombré. C'est très utile pour "
"visualiser le terrain. Vous pouvez éventuellement spécifier l'azimut et "
"l'altitude de la source lumineuse, un facteur d'exagération verticale et un "
"facteur d'échelle pour tenir compte des différences entre les unités "
"verticales et horizontales."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1441
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1612
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1735
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2140
msgid "Input Elevation raster layer"
msgstr "Couche raster d'élévation en entrée"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1447
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1741
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2146
msgid "Band containing the elevation information"
msgstr "Bande contenant les informations d'élévation"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1448
msgid "**Z factor (vertical exaggeration)**"
msgstr "**Facteur Z (exagération verticale)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1449
msgid "``Z_FACTOR``"
msgstr "``Z_FACTOR``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1453
msgid "The factor exaggerates the height of the output elevation raster"
msgstr "Le facteur exagère la hauteur du raster d'élévation en sortie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1456
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2148
msgid "``SCALE``"
msgstr "``SCALE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1460
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2152
msgid "The ratio of vertical units to horizontal units"
msgstr "Le rapport des unités verticales aux unités horizontales"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1461
msgid "**Azimuth of the light**"
msgstr "**Azimut de la lumière**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1462
msgid "``AZIMUTH``"
msgstr "``AZIMUTH``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1465
msgid "Default: 315.0"
msgstr "Par défaut : 315.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1466
msgid ""
"Defines the azimuth of the light shining on the elevation raster in degrees."
" If it comes from the top of the raster the value is 0, if it comes from the"
" east it is 90 a.s.o."
msgstr ""
"Définit l'azimut de la lumière qui brille sur le raster d'élévation en "
"degrés. Si elle vient du haut du raster, la valeur est 0, si elle vient de "
"l'est, elle est de 90 a.s.o."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1470
msgid "**Altitude of the light**"
msgstr "**Altitude de la lumière**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1471
msgid "``ALTITUDE``"
msgstr "``ALTITUDE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1474
msgid "Default: 45.0"
msgstr "Par défaut : 45.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1475
msgid ""
"Defines the altitude of the light, in degrees. 90 if the light comes from "
"above the elevation raster, 0 if it is raking light."
msgstr ""
"Définit l'altitude de la lumière, en degrés. 90 si la lumière vient du "
"dessus du raster d'élévation, 0 s'il s'agit de lumière rasante."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1484
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:2165
msgid "**Use Zevenbergen&Thorne formula (instead of the Horn's one)**"
msgstr ""
"**Utiliser la formule de Zevenbergen & Thorne (au lieu de celle de Horn)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1490
msgid "**Combined shading**"
msgstr "**Ombrage combiné**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1491
msgid "``COMBINED``"
msgstr "``COMBINED``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1496
msgid "**Multidirectional shading**"
msgstr "**Ombrage multidirectionnel**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1497
msgid "``MULTIDIRECTIONAL``"
msgstr "``MULTIDIRECTIONAL``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1502
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/gdal/rasteranalysis.rst:1562
